    <h1>California Pizza Kitchen Gluten-Free Crust Ingredients: A Comprehensive Guide</h1>

    <p>California Pizza Kitchen (CPK) has long been a favorite among pizza lovers for its innovative and diverse menu. For those with gluten sensitivities or celiac disease, CPK offers a gluten-free crust option that allows everyone to enjoy their delicious pizzas. In this article, we’ll dive deep into the ingredients used in CPK’s gluten-free crust, explore its nutritional profile, and answer some frequently asked questions.</p>

    <h2>What Makes CPK’s Gluten-Free Crust Unique?</h2>

    <p>CPK’s gluten-free crust is crafted to provide a delicious and safe alternative for those who need to avoid gluten. The crust is made from a blend of gluten-free flours and other ingredients that mimic the texture and taste of traditional pizza crust. The result is a crust that is both flavorful and satisfying, without compromising on quality or safety.</p>

    <h2>Ingredients in CPK’s Gluten-Free Crust</h2>

    <p>The ingredients used in CPK’s gluten-free crust are carefully selected to ensure they meet the needs of gluten-sensitive individuals. Below is a detailed breakdown of the ingredients:</p>

    <table>
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Ingredient</th>
                <th>Purpose</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>Rice Flour</td>
                <td>Provides the base for the crust, offering a light and airy texture.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Tapioca Starch</td>
                <td>Helps to bind the ingredients together and adds chewiness to the crust.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Potato Starch</td>
                <td>Adds moisture and helps to create a soft texture.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Egg Whites</td>
                <td>Provides structure and helps the crust rise during baking.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Olive Oil</td>
                <td>Adds richness and helps to create a crispy exterior.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Xanthan Gum</td>
                <td>Acts as a binder and helps to mimic the elasticity of gluten.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Yeast</td>
                <td>Helps the dough rise and adds flavor.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Salt</td>
                <td>Enhances the flavor of the crust.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Sugar</td>
                <td>Feeds the yeast and adds a slight sweetness to the crust.</td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>

