    <h2>FAQs About CPK’s Gluten-Free Crust</h2>

    <div class="faq">
        <h3>Is CPK’s gluten-free crust safe for people with celiac disease?</h3>
        <p>Yes, CPK’s gluten-free crust is made in a dedicated gluten-free facility to prevent cross-contamination, making it safe for individuals with celiac disease.</p>

        <h3>Does CPK’s gluten-free crust contain any allergens?</h3>
        <p>CPK’s gluten-free crust contains eggs, which are a common allergen. It is also processed in a facility that handles tree nuts, so cross-contamination is possible.</p>

        <h3>How does CPK’s gluten-free crust compare to traditional crust in terms of taste?</h3>
        <p>CPK’s gluten-free crust is designed to closely mimic the taste and texture of traditional pizza crust. While it may have a slightly different texture, many customers find it to be just as delicious.</p>

        <h3>Can I order CPK’s gluten-free crust online?</h3>
        <p>Yes, CPK offers online ordering for their gluten-free pizzas, allowing you to enjoy their gluten-free crust from the comfort of your home.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>Conclusion</h2>

    <p>California Pizza Kitchen’s gluten-free crust is a testament to the brand’s commitment to inclusivity and quality. By using a carefully selected blend of gluten-free flours and other ingredients, CPK has created a crust that is not only safe for those with gluten sensitivities but also delicious and satisfying. Whether you’re dining in or ordering online, CPK’s gluten-free crust ensures that everyone can enjoy a slice of their favorite pizza without compromise.</p>

